[p 
	"This game is not too interesting as a speed run, but it could potentially be accepted in the Vault category, if it was played as fast as possible. However, there appears to be some possible improvements to this movie. Spikestuff commented on some of them in the discussion topic. The intro menu is not optimal, and the bosses could be killed quicker by more precise shooting. Also, there appears to be some lag when there are a lot of enemies on screen, which could possibly be avoided by killing the enemies quicker. For this reason, I am rejecting this movie.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Also, while not technically a requirement for the Vault category, the autoscrolling sections of the game could be a lot more interesting. For example, you could kill everything at the last second, not kill anything and just dodge (as long as this does not cause lag), or move the ship in interesting patterns. At times, this movie looks like a regular human playing it - firing blindly and missing shots, and letting some enemies get away.
	$LF
]p
